00:00:19,190 --> 00:00:24,090
Military Prosecutor Doberman

8
00:00:55,750 --> 00:00:57,420
Drop the gun.

9
00:00:58,490 --> 00:01:00,350
Drop the gun, bastard.

10
00:01:00,350 --> 00:01:03,250
Mom. Mom.

11
00:01:03,250 --> 00:01:06,230
What are you going to do? What are you going to do, bastard?

12
00:01:12,190 --> 00:01:15,230
One Week Earlier

13
00:01:16,020 --> 00:01:20,980
However, as my father's daughter,

14
00:01:21,920 --> 00:01:24,930
it was an incredibly hard decision.

15
00:01:27,650 --> 00:01:29,720
It was tough.

16
00:01:31,220 --> 00:01:37,830
And I'm sorry for not being able to tell Prosecutor Do Bae Man in advance.

17
00:01:38,440 --> 00:01:41,710
- I am deeply sorry.
- That's enough. Stop.

18
00:01:44,310 --> 00:01:46,890
You may stop talking.

19
00:01:56,170 --> 00:01:59,660
I don't need all the other reasons.

20
00:01:59,660 --> 00:02:04,950
So you can stop talking, Cha Wu In.

21
00:02:19,220 --> 00:02:21,100
What are you two doing?

22
00:02:21,100 --> 00:02:23,030
Unity.

23
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:28,560
We're in the middle of clearing up the court records.

24
00:02:28,560 --> 00:02:33,770
In any case, in every trial you always assign me something to do, huh?

25
00:02:33,770 --> 00:02:36,390
It was you who called the division commander's adjutant as a witness, wasn't it?

26
00:02:36,390 --> 00:02:40,780
It was for me to do my best as a military prosecutor, as I always said.

27
00:02:40,780 --> 00:02:45,930
Pros Cha has completed another tough trial. You should compliment her.

28
00:02:45,930 --> 00:02:48,210
All right.

29
00:02:48,210 --> 00:02:50,790
Cha Wu In, you are amazing! It was amazing.

30
00:02:50,790 --> 00:02:56,120
Look here. Now there isn't anyone in the 4th Division who doesn't know her.

31
00:02:57,160 --> 00:03:01,020
Detective Do Su Kyeong will be visiting your office soon for trial material.

32
00:03:01,020 --> 00:03:05,020
Huh? Auntie... Detective Do?

33
00:03:05,020 --> 00:03:10,130
Jeez. I should practice being brave. Seriously.

34
00:03:10,130 --> 00:03:13,120
Oh, shut it. I mean...

35
00:03:13,120 --> 00:03:15,640
His inner voice is rather loud.

36
00:03:17,850 --> 00:03:20,880
Although I expected that No Hwa Yeong would hit Hong Mu Seop hard,

37
00:03:20,880 --> 00:03:23,270
I didn't think it would be so soon.

38
00:03:23,270 --> 00:03:27,710
A full-scale war will break out within the Patriotic Society, won't it?

39
00:03:27,710 --> 00:03:30,710
It's disappointing one person is being excluded from the hostilities.

40
00:03:30,710 --> 00:03:34,850
Yong Mun Gu. Now that he was stabbed in the back at the trial,

41
00:03:34,850 --> 00:03:38,210
he will show his naked face to No Hwa Yeong.

42
00:03:38,210 --> 00:03:43,320
I am looking forward to how Yong Mun Gu, who was waiting for a rift between No Hwa Yeong and the Patriotic Society,

43
00:03:43,320 --> 00:03:45,490
will approach No Hwa Yeong.

44
00:03:48,650 --> 00:03:53,580
One of the items confiscated from me in the search and seizure must be an SSD hard drive.

45
00:03:53,580 --> 00:03:56,960
- That's my response.
- What's in the hard drive?

46
00:03:56,960 --> 00:04:01,550
A fatal blow to No Hwa Yeong.

47
00:04:07,210 --> 00:04:10,000
Prosecutor Kang

48
00:04:11,820 --> 00:04:13,420
Yes, Seonbaenim.

49
00:04:13,420 --> 00:04:17,610
Thanks for the quick search and seizure warrant for Kang's Solution.

50
00:04:17,610 --> 00:04:21,820
As you instructed, we're going through the allegations thoroughly.

51
00:04:21,820 --> 00:04:25,430
There's a new factor, so could you slow it down a little?

52
00:04:25,430 --> 00:04:26,940
Pardon?

53
00:04:26,940 --> 00:04:31,180
Oh. I understand what you're saying.

54
00:04:31,180 --> 00:04:33,340
But the thing is...

55
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:43,900
Is it possible for me to see one item among the items seized from Kang's Solution?

56
00:05:02,110 --> 00:05:04,620
Are you still wearing that watch?

57
00:05:04,620 --> 00:05:09,110
It saved my life. I exchanged it for my life.

58
00:05:16,550 --> 00:05:18,570
Episode 13

59
00:05:38,550 --> 00:05:39,990
You're here?

60
00:05:39,990 --> 00:05:43,830
Hey, No Hwa Yeong. Try to explain yourself to me right now, Bitch!

61
00:05:43,830 --> 00:05:48,550
Why did you attend the trial for the corps commander and ruin the trial?

62
00:05:48,550 --> 00:05:52,800
If you can't convince me here and now, prepare for the worst!

63
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:56,540
You said you would use both a sword and shield and guaranteed he would win.

64
00:05:56,540 --> 00:06:00,940
Didn't you hear what the Minister just said. He said to explain immediately.

65
00:06:00,940 --> 00:06:05,530
Calm your anger and take a look at this first, Minister.

66
00:06:05,530 --> 00:06:08,090
What use is this article?

67
00:06:08,090 --> 00:06:11,220
Read it to the Minister, Vice Corps Commander.

68
00:06:11,220 --> 00:06:14,350
This little...

69
00:06:18,360 --> 00:06:22,520
"Commander No Hwa Yeong's courageous action on behalf of the two non-commissioned officers,

70
00:06:22,520 --> 00:06:27,220
who suffered incredibly, was a spark."

71
00:06:29,330 --> 00:06:33,460
"Thanks to that, the divisive blame for the army's irresponsibility

72
00:06:33,460 --> 00:06:37,790
has been dispelled throughout the country."

73
00:06:37,790 --> 00:06:41,050
The next part is important.

74
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:47,070
"A key official at the Blue House (President of Korea's office) said

75
00:06:47,070 --> 00:06:51,880
Minister Lee Jae Sik's initiation of a drive to revolutionize military culture,

76
00:06:51,880 --> 00:06:55,850
which even included setting up a special investigation team, should be commended."

77
00:06:55,850 --> 00:07:02,490
M-M-Minister, the situation which you worried about has been completely reversed.

78
00:07:02,490 --> 00:07:07,340
Minister, have you also known about the sadistic nature of the corps commander,

79
00:07:07,340 --> 00:07:10,640
who treats his men as disposable for a long time?

80
00:07:10,640 --> 00:07:13,380
You just pretended not to know.

81
00:07:13,380 --> 00:07:16,670
Vice Corps Commander, who was closer than anyone to Corps Commander Hong

82
00:07:16,670 --> 00:07:19,590
will not be able to deny knowledge.

83
00:07:19,590 --> 00:07:25,210
My subordinates cannot be only ones who were abused.

84
00:07:25,210 --> 00:07:30,000
This time we must self-purify within the army

85
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:34,290
and you must put a period on it.

86
00:07:34,290 --> 00:07:36,250
A period?

87
00:07:37,170 --> 00:07:43,410
You must remove the corps commander from the Patriotic Society.

88
00:07:46,580 --> 00:07:52,180
I'll handle all the risky situation of dealing with people.

89
00:07:52,180 --> 00:07:54,440
The only thing you have to do

90
00:07:55,770 --> 00:07:59,110
is take care of showing off.

91
00:08:07,500 --> 00:08:09,520
Get in a little bit later.

92
00:08:20,020 --> 00:08:23,710
I never expected the situation would turn around like this.

93
00:08:23,710 --> 00:08:26,960
Did the division commander really testify for the sake of her subordinates?

94
00:08:26,960 --> 00:08:30,570
Or was this intended to demolish the corps commander?

95
00:08:30,570 --> 00:08:33,860
I think it was the latter.

96
00:08:33,860 --> 00:08:38,950
One thing is obvious. She is sitting on top of my head

97
00:08:38,950 --> 00:08:41,560
trying to manipulating me.

98
00:08:41,560 --> 00:08:43,460
That's right. Right!

99
00:08:43,460 --> 00:08:49,030
I think you raised a fire fox with a thousand tails.

100
00:08:49,030 --> 00:08:53,970
At this time, what do you think about cutting her off also?

101
00:08:53,970 --> 00:08:59,610
Idiot. That's why you will never beat her.

102
00:08:59,610 --> 00:09:04,310
Don't you see it's turning out like this because I can't get rid of her?

103
00:09:04,310 --> 00:09:07,260
Oh, No Hwa Yeong. Damn.

104
00:09:07,260 --> 00:09:12,060
So what will you do now, Minister?

105
00:09:12,060 --> 00:09:14,470
May I ask you something?

106
00:09:14,470 --> 00:09:16,080
What is it?

107
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:22,460
I wonder how you hide your feelings like that in front of No Hwa Yeong.

108
00:09:22,460 --> 00:09:25,670
The person who murdered your parents is right in front of you.

109
00:09:28,500 --> 00:09:33,680
There are times when I also want to personally strangle her immediately.

110
00:09:33,680 --> 00:09:38,760
Just as you wanted to end everything with a single bullet.

111
00:09:41,590 --> 00:09:44,790
Not long ago, my father appeared in a dream.

112
00:09:44,790 --> 00:09:48,880
It was a very long time since I last saw him. My father.

113
00:09:49,650 --> 00:09:53,490
What did he say?

114
00:09:54,490 --> 00:09:56,890
"You must win

115
00:09:58,360 --> 00:10:00,730
and you must win righteously."

116
00:10:03,390 --> 00:10:05,060
Let's go in.

117
00:10:05,060 --> 00:10:10,300
No Hwa Yeong said something strange to me.

118
00:10:10,300 --> 00:10:11,980
What did she say?

119
00:10:11,980 --> 00:10:17,060
She said there was something I don't know about in her relationship with my dad.

120
00:10:17,060 --> 00:10:21,630
But the two never had any relationship.

121
00:10:21,630 --> 00:10:24,720
Even in my dad's keepsakes I don't see a single photo.

122
00:10:25,560 --> 00:10:28,360
Don't pay too much attention to what she says.

123
00:10:31,310 --> 00:10:32,850
Let's go in.

124
00:10:48,060 --> 00:10:50,670
I'm saying there are things you don't know.

125
00:10:50,670 --> 00:10:53,230
You were too young at that time.

126
00:10:53,230 --> 00:10:59,260
We could've had a completely different relationship than now.

127
00:11:46,510 --> 00:11:49,430
Praying Major No Hwa Yeong has peace. From Cha Ho Cheol.

128
00:11:50,390 --> 00:11:52,170
Yes, I've arrived.
[4th Infantry Division]

129
00:11:52,170 --> 00:11:56,870
Chairman Cha died on the scene. There was a passenger with him.

130
00:11:56,870 --> 00:11:59,680
Passenger? Who is it?

131
00:11:59,680 --> 00:12:03,170
It was his daughter. They say she had come back from the United States three days ago.

132
00:12:03,170 --> 00:12:06,030
Did she also die with him?

133
00:12:06,030 --> 00:12:08,300
She is unconscious.

134
00:12:08,950 --> 00:12:12,290
Looking at the scene, it looks like there isn't any chance.

135
00:12:13,990 --> 00:12:15,510
General?

136
00:12:23,680 --> 00:12:25,950
Thank you. Thank you.

137
00:12:25,950 --> 00:12:28,530
- I'll make good use of it.
- Tae Nam, thank you.

138
00:12:28,530 --> 00:12:30,360
Thank you.

139
00:12:36,980 --> 00:12:40,320
Lawyer Yong, how did you get in here? Civilians are prohibited from entering.

140
00:12:40,320 --> 00:12:43,540
This is the general's division. Nothing is impossible.

141
00:12:43,540 --> 00:12:46,590
You called me a few days ago. That's why I came.

142
00:12:46,590 --> 00:12:49,550
Then did Mother send you here?

143
00:12:52,830 --> 00:12:56,600
I guess not. My mother wouldn't do that.

144
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:59,770
When I think about it, I don't have anyone but Lawyer Yong.

145
00:12:59,770 --> 00:13:03,420
Chairman, you're having a tough time in the army, right?

146
00:13:04,130 --> 00:13:08,610
Now that you have started military service, let me give you a tip.

147
00:13:10,020 --> 00:13:12,610
- Tip?
- You don't understand the army, do you?

148
00:13:12,610 --> 00:13:14,810
How does one understand this place? How?

149
00:13:14,810 --> 00:13:16,490
That's why it is hard.

150
00:13:16,490 --> 00:13:21,040
the military is not a place to understand. It's a place to give up.

151
00:13:21,040 --> 00:13:24,120
When you said you'd give me a tip, how can you be saying that?

152
00:13:24,120 --> 00:13:29,160
Never understanding a monster like your mother and ultimately giving up.

153
00:13:29,160 --> 00:13:31,290
Just like you now.

154
00:13:31,290 --> 00:13:33,550
You... just now...

155
00:13:33,550 --> 00:13:35,700
Your having not gone crazy under your mom,

156
00:13:35,700 --> 00:13:40,540
and not going crazy here, too, is amazing, Tae Nam.

157
00:13:58,120 --> 00:14:00,020
No Tae Nam.

158
00:14:00,020 --> 00:14:04,050
- Private No Tae Nam.
- Follow me for a personal interview.

159
00:14:13,260 --> 00:14:17,090
Why did you collapse last time you were on guard duty?

160
00:14:18,580 --> 00:14:22,340
Sergeant An Su Ho was the paired superior for you.

161
00:14:23,360 --> 00:14:25,430
Did something happen?

162
00:14:26,790 --> 00:14:32,280
Stop whining like a baby, you punk!

163
00:14:34,150 --> 00:14:37,040
You want to know something really funny?

164
00:14:41,930 --> 00:14:47,030
No matter how much I torment you, the world won't believe it.

165
00:14:47,960 --> 00:14:50,720
They'll think the opposite.

166
00:15:05,670 --> 00:15:09,440
It was nothing, sir. I just felt dizzy for a moment.

167
00:15:09,440 --> 00:15:14,060
Are you sure? This won't become an issue later, right?

168
00:15:14,950 --> 00:15:16,900
Yes, sir.

169
00:15:16,900 --> 00:15:20,230
We're good then. You can leave.

170
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:32,520
Did you do as I told you?

171
00:15:34,810 --> 00:15:37,540
I said nothing happened.

172
00:15:37,540 --> 00:15:39,630
Good job.

173
00:15:40,680 --> 00:15:45,540
You even fixed the way you talked. You sound like a real soldier now.

174
00:15:45,540 --> 00:15:51,410
Don't forget what I said. If anything happens here, everyone will suspect you first.

175
00:15:51,410 --> 00:15:53,430
Because...

176
00:15:54,240 --> 00:15:57,170
you're No Tae Nam, the deserter.

177
00:16:04,360 --> 00:16:07,120
That bastard.

178
00:16:17,750 --> 00:16:21,290
Why are you here instead of the Minister?

179
00:16:23,640 --> 00:16:27,490
He has some important business, so I came instead.

180
00:16:27,490 --> 00:16:33,430
What could be more important than me? The Patriotic Society is at risk of being uprooted!

181
00:16:33,430 --> 00:16:36,690
I guess you still need a reality check.

182
00:16:36,690 --> 00:16:38,930
What? You little—

183
00:16:38,930 --> 00:16:43,140
I wasn't going to say this.

184
00:16:43,140 --> 00:16:47,500
The minister has been invited to a luncheon at the Blue House

185
00:16:47,500 --> 00:16:52,060
to show him support in the special investigation of abuse of power in the military.

186
00:16:52,060 --> 00:16:57,760
Which is why I came in his place to deliver his message.

187
00:16:57,760 --> 00:17:01,720
He ordered me to deliver these words.

188
00:17:05,290 --> 00:17:08,560
It's an old saying.

189
00:17:08,560 --> 00:17:14,290
Drive out what's unclean to bring in what's clean.

190
00:17:14,290 --> 00:17:17,130
The Minister has spoken.

191
00:17:17,130 --> 00:17:20,920
He also said this is the path that the Patriotic Society must take.

192
00:17:20,920 --> 00:17:22,570
Goodbye then.

193
00:17:23,720 --> 00:17:29,610
You, Heo Kang In. How could you insult me like this too?

194
00:17:31,910 --> 00:17:36,880
A soldier is loyal to his superior only when he's stronger.

195
00:17:36,880 --> 00:17:43,420
Let's be honest. It's not like you were the backbone of the Patriotic Society.

196
00:17:58,200 --> 00:18:02,620
A joint investigation with military prosecutors and civilian police. This is right up my alley.

197
00:18:02,620 --> 00:18:04,990
Now that we've blown the corps commander away...

198
00:18:06,720 --> 00:18:10,610
it feels like justice has been served.

199
00:18:12,270 --> 00:18:16,700
Does this mean I was born to be a soldier too?

200
00:18:20,320 --> 00:18:25,460
Why the long-face though? Are you feeling bitter?

201
00:18:25,460 --> 00:18:29,800
Well, I wouldn't say bitter.

202
00:18:29,800 --> 00:18:35,460
Listen, Auntie. Do you know the agony of waiting for the higher-ups' orders after a trial?

203
00:18:35,460 --> 00:18:37,930
Do you have any idea?

204
00:18:39,890 --> 00:18:41,230
- Unity.
- Unity.

205
00:18:41,230 --> 00:18:45,690
You're here. I brought this just in case you need it to investigate Hong Gyeong Ok.

206
00:18:45,690 --> 00:18:49,620
- Daebak.
- What now? What did you bring?

207
00:18:49,620 --> 00:18:53,960
Cha Wu In, you always act before me. That's your problem!

208
00:18:53,960 --> 00:18:58,050
You don't know how lucky you are to have a subordinate like her.

209
00:19:02,890 --> 00:19:04,810
This is Seo Ju Hyeok.

210
00:19:04,810 --> 00:19:07,990
Division Commander! Unity!

211
00:19:07,990 --> 00:19:11,040
Sorry? Thank you.

212
00:19:11,040 --> 00:19:15,080
Thank you, Division Commander. Unity!

213
00:19:21,650 --> 00:19:25,430
Cha Wu In. I'm getting promoted one rank.

214
00:19:25,430 --> 00:19:29,210
The Division Commander has signed on it.

215
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:32,990
- Congratulations, sir.
- Yes!

216
00:19:35,550 --> 00:19:36,990
- Let's wrap it up now.
- Okay.

217
00:19:36,990 --> 00:19:38,490
All right.

218
00:19:50,990 --> 00:19:53,490
Where did you go so early?

219
00:19:54,570 --> 00:19:56,900
I'll tell you after lunch.

220
00:19:56,900 --> 00:20:00,400
Shall we eat out? What do you want?

221
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:03,410
I'm not sure. Let's head out first.

222
00:20:03,410 --> 00:20:05,930
Did Sang Gi and Section Chief Ahn go somewhere?

223
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:16,220
They're going to get lunch? Together?

224
00:20:16,220 --> 00:20:18,850
They didn't even think to look for us, right?

225
00:20:18,850 --> 00:20:21,000
The curiosity is killing me.

226
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:23,380
We'll have to confirm it with our own eyes then.

227
00:20:23,380 --> 00:20:25,930
Yes, I agree.

228
00:20:30,130 --> 00:20:32,620
It's my treat today.

229
00:20:32,620 --> 00:20:35,500
Hey, Prosecutor Cha.

230
00:20:36,220 --> 00:20:38,020
What's wrong?

231
00:20:38,020 --> 00:20:42,590
This is it? I would've ordered a course meal then.

232
00:20:42,590 --> 00:20:44,320
Order a tangsuyuk (Chinese sweet sour pork) for me too.

233
00:20:44,320 --> 00:20:47,730
Yes, okay, I'll do that.

234
00:20:49,230 --> 00:20:51,280
No, wait.

235
00:20:52,500 --> 00:20:59,560
♫ hold on the moments which are becoming blurred one by one ♫

236
00:20:59,560 --> 00:21:02,940
This is your reward for completing your second hunt.

237
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:05,840
Enjoy your meal.

238
00:21:05,840 --> 00:21:09,510
Yes, thank you, Master.

239
00:21:10,330 --> 00:21:12,310
Oh, wait.

240
00:21:12,310 --> 00:21:15,700
Chili powder is a must with jjajangmyeon (Chinese black bean noodles).

241
00:21:15,700 --> 00:21:17,800
I don't really like red stuff.

242
00:21:18,460 --> 00:21:20,520
Enjoy it.

243
00:21:20,520 --> 00:21:23,740
Those two. The way they look at each other has changed.

244
00:21:23,740 --> 00:21:26,060
It's always like that with dating in the workplace.

245
00:21:26,060 --> 00:21:28,380
Everyone knows except for themselves.

246
00:21:28,380 --> 00:21:33,220
Those two don't know. They really don't.

247
00:21:33,220 --> 00:21:35,740
Hold on a minute.

248
00:21:39,870 --> 00:21:43,920
Gosh. Section Chief Ahn, the game is over.

249
00:21:43,920 --> 00:21:47,490
- They're sharing their meals.
- What?

250
00:21:47,490 --> 00:21:51,730
We were too busy with work, so we didn't pay enough attention to them.

251
00:21:51,730 --> 00:21:55,230
All right, what should we eat? Shall we order jjajangmyeon and jjambbong  (spicy seafood noodles)?

252
00:21:55,230 --> 00:21:57,340
When I'm depressed...

253
00:21:58,600 --> 00:22:00,400
You eat ulmyeon*?
(Noodles in thick broth, Korean sounds like "cry.")

254
00:22:00,400 --> 00:22:02,500
When I have a lot on my mind?

255
00:22:02,500 --> 00:22:04,460
- You eat fried rice.
- Tang, tang, tang!

256
00:22:04,460 --> 00:22:07,030
Tangsuyuk! It hurts.

257
00:22:14,380 --> 00:22:17,040
- Enjoy your meal.
- Thank you.

258
00:22:17,040 --> 00:22:19,100
Lieutenant Colonel Seo Ju Hyeok.

259
00:22:19,100 --> 00:22:23,350
So cool. I'm so proud of myself.

260
00:22:26,200 --> 00:22:28,860
I prepared it for you.

261
00:22:28,860 --> 00:22:30,730
Eat a lot.

262
00:22:30,730 --> 00:22:34,530
Congratulations on getting promoted, Honey.

263
00:22:34,530 --> 00:22:36,840
Love shot.

264
00:22:38,920 --> 00:22:42,760
Amazing. Take a bite, Honey. No, you first.

265
00:22:42,760 --> 00:22:45,100
Okay, thank you.

266
00:22:46,570 --> 00:22:48,780
It's delicious.

267
00:22:55,470 --> 00:23:00,900
I have no one to share this happy moment with me.

268
00:23:01,730 --> 00:23:08,670
Who will help this successful lonely man?

269
00:23:16,470 --> 00:23:19,880
What a beautiful day. It must be spring.

270
00:23:19,880 --> 00:23:21,360
Unity.

271
00:23:22,850 --> 00:23:26,600
What were you going to tell me earlier?

272
00:23:26,600 --> 00:23:29,530
Things are going as we predicted.

273
00:23:29,530 --> 00:23:31,340
You mean the Patriotic Society?

274
00:23:31,340 --> 00:23:35,910
Yes. Hong Mu Seop asked for me.

275
00:23:35,910 --> 00:23:40,850
I'm impressed, Do Bae Man. You got me locked up for three years

276
00:23:40,850 --> 00:23:46,000
just for having my subordinates run a few errands for me and hitting them a couple of times.

277
00:23:48,020 --> 00:23:53,640
It was a big win for me since I revealed your true self and stripped you of your rank.

278
00:23:53,640 --> 00:23:59,730
Also, we're getting a ton of reports from soldiers who were abused by you.

279
00:23:59,730 --> 00:24:05,910
Think of the three years as an appetizer. The real meal hasn't even started.

280
00:24:05,910 --> 00:24:12,190
I found out why you did this even after you promised your loyalty to me.

281
00:24:12,190 --> 00:24:14,440
I expected you would.

282
00:24:14,440 --> 00:24:19,170
You were the son of my direct subordinate investigators.

283
00:24:19,170 --> 00:24:22,340
I was your target from the very beginning.

284
00:24:22,340 --> 00:24:27,950
You can't forget about No Hwa Yeong who benefitted from my hard work.

285
00:24:27,950 --> 00:24:31,880
- No Hwa Yeong.
- Also don't forget about the Patriotic Society either.

286
00:24:35,900 --> 00:24:41,550
From now on, the military prosecutor will not use honorifics in speaking to you, a criminal, got it?

287
00:24:41,550 --> 00:24:44,310
You. The Patriotic Society abandoned you, right?

288
00:24:44,310 --> 00:24:46,410
Why do you think that?

289
00:24:46,410 --> 00:24:48,400
Because you called me.

290
00:24:48,400 --> 00:24:52,990
You're probably trying to find a way to save yourself since you were abandoned by them.

291
00:24:52,990 --> 00:24:56,290
Isn't that right, Corps Commander?

292
00:24:57,060 --> 00:24:59,580
Your real target is No Hwa Yeong, isn't it?

293
00:24:59,580 --> 00:25:05,340
I just got caught in that process. It was No Hwa Yeong who killed your parents.

294
00:25:06,270 --> 00:25:11,030
You must know that she took control of Cha Ho Cheol's company too?

295
00:25:11,030 --> 00:25:16,500
So aren't you curious about why she even killed him too?

296
00:25:16,500 --> 00:25:19,890
She could've just taken the company and kicked him out.

297
00:25:21,390 --> 00:25:25,340
Tell me, what did Hong Mu Seop say?

298
00:25:25,340 --> 00:25:29,410
Is there another reason why she killed Chairman Cha?

299
00:25:29,410 --> 00:25:33,670
Cha Ho Cheol threatened No Hwa Yeong.

300
00:25:33,670 --> 00:25:36,710
That's basically threatening the Patriotic Society.

301
00:25:36,710 --> 00:25:42,790
Cha Ho Cheol gathered documents of corruption within the Patriotic Society like crazy.

302
00:25:42,790 --> 00:25:46,270
It was like a Patriotic Society X-File. That was what we called it.

303
00:25:46,270 --> 00:25:49,550
Patriotic Society X-File?

304
00:25:49,550 --> 00:25:54,380
That was completed about six years ago. He used that to threaten No Hwa Yeong?

305
00:25:54,380 --> 00:25:59,380
That's right. If that X-File had been revealed then,

306
00:25:59,380 --> 00:26:02,310
then the Patriotic Society wouldn't have existed up to now.

307
00:26:04,360 --> 00:26:09,130
No Hwa Yeong silenced everything and took control of the company.

308
00:26:09,130 --> 00:26:12,230
She got rid of Cha Ho Cheol who was a pain.

309
00:26:12,230 --> 00:26:15,790
You were right, Do Bae Man.

310
00:26:16,720 --> 00:26:19,460
The Patriotic Society abandoned me.

311
00:26:19,460 --> 00:26:26,640
I must see them sink, from in here, with my own eyes.

312
00:26:27,370 --> 00:26:30,430
Father tried to destroy the Patriotic Society?

313
00:26:30,430 --> 00:26:34,100
The X-File of the Patriotic Society that your father made.

314
00:26:34,100 --> 00:26:37,880
Apparently he threatened No Hwa Yeong and the Patriotic Society with that.

315
00:26:39,190 --> 00:26:42,330
How much of his claim can we trust?

316
00:26:42,330 --> 00:26:46,400
Did your father leave anything behind—

317
00:26:46,400 --> 00:26:51,450
You're curious if there was anything related to the Patriotic Society X-File?

318
00:26:51,450 --> 00:26:54,410
No, there wasn't.

319
00:26:54,410 --> 00:26:58,650
I thought so. There's no way you would miss it.

320
00:26:59,750 --> 00:27:05,380
Then there are three possibilities. That file has disappeared forever,

321
00:27:05,380 --> 00:27:10,840
No Hwa Yeong has it, or someone else does.

322
00:27:10,840 --> 00:27:13,120
I doubt No Hwa Yeong has it.

323
00:27:13,120 --> 00:27:20,000
If she had taken it from Father, she would have used it to secure a much higher position.

324
00:27:20,870 --> 00:27:22,580
Hold on.

325
00:27:23,210 --> 00:27:28,700
I just thought of a person who could get his hands on the X-File.

326
00:27:30,490 --> 00:27:34,170
It can't be... right?

327
00:27:35,160 --> 00:27:39,970
I doubt it. It can't be No Tae Nam.

328
00:27:39,970 --> 00:27:41,430
Shoot!

329
00:27:44,770 --> 00:27:49,100
- What? Say that again.
- What is it?

330
00:27:49,100 --> 00:27:52,610
I did everything as I was told. I even went in the sleeping bag.

331
00:27:52,610 --> 00:27:55,820
But I won't have you insult my mother. Apologize.

332
00:27:55,820 --> 00:27:58,500
Gosh, take a look at this punk.

333
00:27:58,500 --> 00:28:00,610
You know how to put on a show too.

334
00:28:01,470 --> 00:28:06,730
Hey. I'm the only villain in your eyes, right?

335
00:28:06,730 --> 00:28:09,220
But it's all your fault.

336
00:28:09,220 --> 00:28:14,020
Why did you put up with it? It only made it more fun.

337
00:28:14,790 --> 00:28:17,130
You see! This is what I'm talking about. This is it!

338
00:28:17,130 --> 00:28:20,460
I can't do this any more once I'm discharged.

339
00:28:20,460 --> 00:28:22,920
- Should I just enlist again?
- Yes, sir!

340
00:28:22,920 --> 00:28:24,670
I think you should do that.

341
00:28:32,550 --> 00:28:35,730
You shouldn't have put up with it. Why did you?

342
00:28:35,730 --> 00:28:37,600
Shall we finish our conversation from before?

343
00:28:37,600 --> 00:28:41,980
Pyeon. Your mom sells tteokbokki (spicy ricecake) at Seonmun Station, right?

344
00:28:41,980 --> 00:28:47,780
I went to try it while I was on leave so I can make a scene once I'm discharged.

345
00:28:48,470 --> 00:28:52,610
- It seemed like she hurt her legs.
- Aigoo.

346
00:28:52,610 --> 00:28:54,350
You f***ing bastard.

347
00:28:55,950 --> 00:28:59,660
Hey, I'm kidding. It's a joke.

348
00:29:00,590 --> 00:29:05,640
- Pyeon. You can't tell the difference between a joke and the real thing?
- Just let it go.

349
00:29:05,640 --> 00:29:10,430
Continue to put up with everything while you're here. For your mother's sake.

350
00:29:11,320 --> 00:29:13,420
- Let's go.
- Yes, sir.

351
00:29:13,420 --> 00:29:17,310
- Let's go!
- Hey, over here.

352
00:29:17,310 --> 00:29:20,680
- Give me the ball.
- Nice.

353
00:29:48,760 --> 00:29:50,300
I can see clearly.

354
00:29:50,300 --> 00:29:53,100
Don't put up with it from now on.

355
00:30:12,700 --> 00:30:14,450
Are you sure you left it here?

356
00:30:14,450 --> 00:30:17,060
You didn't leave it at your residence?

357
00:30:17,830 --> 00:30:20,210
CEO Kang must've taken it.

358
00:30:24,180 --> 00:30:27,820
The receiver cannot be reached. You will be directed to voicemail.

359
00:30:29,440 --> 00:30:30,580
The receiver cannot be reached. You will be directed to voicemail.

360
00:30:30,580 --> 00:30:36,270
Why didn't he tell us? What was he thinking, taking something so important?

361
00:30:36,270 --> 00:30:40,250
He was probably looking for more material since the hard drive had nothing.

362
00:30:40,250 --> 00:30:44,230
This is ridiculous. Darn it.

363
00:30:47,050 --> 00:30:51,840
It just arrived, prosecutor Kang. I'll see you at the headquarters soon.

364
00:31:21,940 --> 00:31:26,010
Even when you framed Chairman Cha Ho Cheol. I stepped up

365
00:31:26,010 --> 00:31:28,780
and lied in court. It was all

366
00:31:28,780 --> 00:31:32,880
solely for you, Division Commander. That's not all.

367
00:31:32,880 --> 00:31:36,440
Twenty years ago. The accident you caused with the truck.

368
00:31:36,440 --> 00:31:40,520
I'm talking about the accident where you crashed into the young soldier couple.

369
00:31:48,640 --> 00:31:50,400
What is this?

370
00:31:50,400 --> 00:31:54,110
The crimes you committed six years ago as a prosecutor.

371
00:31:54,110 --> 00:31:56,450
It's a recording of my past?

372
00:31:57,150 --> 00:32:00,550
And that's Won Gi Chun's secret safe.

373
00:32:07,600 --> 00:32:11,580
CEO Kang. Did you take Won Gi Chun's file box?

374
00:32:15,480 --> 00:32:19,830
The corruption charges against Chairman Cha Ho Cheol that you framed him with.

375
00:32:19,830 --> 00:32:21,730
Won Gi Chun was collecting this stuff.

376
00:32:21,730 --> 00:32:24,990
He probably kept it to save himself if things went wrong.

377
00:32:24,990 --> 00:32:29,290
CEO Kang. Now that you've turned your back on them, you've become ruthless.

378
00:32:29,290 --> 00:32:32,060
You brought me a present I never could've expected.

379
00:32:34,460 --> 00:32:40,440
I gave you more than you expected. Now it's my turn to receive more than I expected.

380
00:32:40,440 --> 00:32:45,450
I have a meeting with Minister Lee Jae Sik soon. Join us then.

381
00:32:45,450 --> 00:32:51,710
You'll get a picture of what I have envisioned in my head.

382
00:33:00,420 --> 00:33:04,790
Vice President. How is the company doing?

383
00:33:04,790 --> 00:33:09,680
I guess CEO Kang hid it from you. The prosecution came in with a search and seizure warrant.

384
00:33:09,680 --> 00:33:11,530
Search and seizure?

385
00:33:11,530 --> 00:33:17,410
Yes. But luckily we took care of urgent matters, thanks to CEO Yong Mun Gu.

386
00:33:18,170 --> 00:33:22,970
CEO Kang went to IM Defense to meet CEO Yong just now.

387
00:33:25,250 --> 00:33:28,380
Thank you again for the unexpected present.

388
00:33:29,760 --> 00:33:31,410
Keep it up.

389
00:33:32,280 --> 00:33:33,740
Bye.

390
00:33:48,420 --> 00:33:53,000
Haven't we been friends for a long time?

391
00:33:53,610 --> 00:34:00,750
I thought we were the only family we had—someone we could lean on when things got tough.

392
00:34:06,100 --> 00:34:09,320
You don't need my help anymore.

393
00:34:09,320 --> 00:34:11,380
You have Do Bae Man.

394
00:34:12,650 --> 00:34:15,320
You're blaming Prosecutor Do?

395
00:34:16,410 --> 00:34:21,820
I only helped you to repay my debt to Chairman Cha.

396
00:34:21,820 --> 00:34:24,960
But you don't need me anymore.

397
00:34:24,960 --> 00:34:29,280
Also, this is getting exhausting.

398
00:34:29,280 --> 00:34:31,830
You should've told me if your company was struggling.

399
00:34:31,830 --> 00:34:33,780
How could you join hands with Yong Mun Gu?

400
00:34:33,780 --> 00:34:41,380
I gave the files to him to save my employees who are relying solely on me.

401
00:34:42,220 --> 00:34:44,210
Oh, right.

402
00:34:45,240 --> 00:34:49,490
Here. You probably won't need it.

403
00:34:49,490 --> 00:34:52,030
But I can't hold onto it anymore either.

404
00:35:33,080 --> 00:35:35,230
It's okay.

405
00:35:35,230 --> 00:35:37,420
It will be all right.

406
00:35:54,720 --> 00:35:57,650
Do Bae Man

407
00:36:01,080 --> 00:36:03,250
Did you meet CEO Kang?

408
00:36:03,250 --> 00:36:04,970
Yes.

409
00:36:04,970 --> 00:36:07,630
Are you still with him?

410
00:36:07,630 --> 00:36:12,390
CEO Kang has joined hands with Yong Mun Gu.

411
00:36:12,390 --> 00:36:14,380
What?

412
00:36:14,380 --> 00:36:16,060
He betrayed us...

413
00:36:16,060 --> 00:36:19,500
I mean, he betrayed you?

414
00:36:19,500 --> 00:36:22,120
He used his company as his excuse.

415
00:36:22,120 --> 00:36:27,050
I also think he resented me too.

416
00:36:29,570 --> 00:36:32,740
I'm sure Yong Mun Gu approached him first.

417
00:36:32,740 --> 00:36:35,470
He wanted to split us up.

418
00:36:39,060 --> 00:36:42,780
Cha Wu In. Are you crying?

419
00:36:42,780 --> 00:36:45,840
I'll take care of this.

420
00:36:45,840 --> 00:36:49,230
This problem is between me and CEO Kang.

