00:37:12,730 --> 00:37:16,440
♫ But none will ever know ♫

428
00:37:18,050 --> 00:37:23,480
♫ Where did it all go wrong ♫

429
00:37:23,480 --> 00:37:25,120
You little...

430
00:37:25,120 --> 00:37:30,420
♫ I just want to get my life back ♫

431
00:37:32,350 --> 00:37:36,240
Just go. I have nothing to say to you.

432
00:37:36,240 --> 00:37:37,940
We don't ever have to see each other again.

433
00:37:37,940 --> 00:37:39,610
How could you betray Cha Wu In?

434
00:37:39,610 --> 00:37:44,170
Stop talking. I don't want to hear anything that you say.

435
00:37:44,170 --> 00:37:48,540
Tell me. What did Yong Mun Gu offer you?

436
00:37:49,290 --> 00:37:51,280
It was an offer I couldn't refuse.

437
00:37:51,280 --> 00:37:54,220
Just like you in the past. I couldn't refuse it either.

438
00:37:54,220 --> 00:37:57,010
♫ everywhere, all this violence, ♫

439
00:37:57,010 --> 00:37:59,810
I think I paid my price, so leave.

440
00:37:59,810 --> 00:38:04,950
Now that you've sided with Yong Mun Gu, you're our enemy now.

441
00:38:04,950 --> 00:38:08,970
Also, don't ever let Cha Wu In see you again.

442
00:38:08,970 --> 00:38:10,690
I might kill you if you do.

443
00:38:10,690 --> 00:38:14,380
♫ When this light gets dark ♫

444
00:38:15,390 --> 00:38:18,340
♫ I'll ignite ♫

445
00:38:19,220 --> 00:38:22,970
♫ In this long night alone ♫

446
00:38:22,970 --> 00:38:24,880
♫ I who am wandering ♫

447
00:38:24,880 --> 00:38:28,740
♫ Let this madness stop ♫

448
00:38:29,580 --> 00:38:33,460
♫ Oh I will try ♫

449
00:38:33,460 --> 00:38:36,660
♫ Light up the surrounding darkness ♫

450
00:38:36,660 --> 00:38:39,780
You don't need me anymore.

451
00:38:39,780 --> 00:38:44,080
Also, this is getting exhausting.

452
00:38:44,080 --> 00:38:47,850
♫ I'll ignite ♫

453
00:38:47,850 --> 00:38:51,710
♫ beyond this dark night ♫

454
00:38:51,710 --> 00:38:53,620
♫ Will the brilliant day ♫

455
00:38:53,620 --> 00:38:57,830
♫ light up my heart? ♫

456
00:39:21,360 --> 00:39:22,760
Is this the guy?

457
00:39:22,760 --> 00:39:23,960
He is.

458
00:39:23,960 --> 00:39:27,560
It's an honor to meet you, Minister. My name is Kang Ha Jun.

459
00:39:27,560 --> 00:39:29,950
You're not even 30 years old?

460
00:39:29,950 --> 00:39:33,460
You're a very talented man.

461
00:39:33,460 --> 00:39:35,800
I'm trying my best to develop into a good businessman.

462
00:39:35,800 --> 00:39:39,320
I look forward to working with you, sir.

463
00:39:39,320 --> 00:39:42,520
Not only is he extremely smart, he's also talented.

464
00:39:42,520 --> 00:39:43,890
You can count on him.

465
00:39:43,890 --> 00:39:49,980
There's a saying, "It's a waste to give youth to a young man."

466
00:39:49,980 --> 00:39:53,610
Being young can be a big risk too.

467
00:39:53,610 --> 00:39:56,620
But he looks like he's got guts.

468
00:39:56,620 --> 00:39:59,740
He doesn't seem faint-hearted.

469
00:40:02,160 --> 00:40:04,250
I'll vouch for him.

470
00:40:04,250 --> 00:40:08,090
In between the orders you give to IM Defense,

471
00:40:08,090 --> 00:40:11,240
CEO Kang Ha Jun's Kang's Solution will be there.

472
00:40:11,240 --> 00:40:14,370
I will do my best to not cause you and CEO Yong any trouble.

473
00:40:14,370 --> 00:40:17,440
Tell me. What's your relationship with him?

474
00:40:17,440 --> 00:40:18,920
Friends?

475
00:40:18,920 --> 00:40:24,170
I've never seen business between friends end well.

476
00:40:24,170 --> 00:40:29,820
I'll become friends with CEO Yong through this business.

477
00:40:37,980 --> 00:40:40,170
- I want to look indifferent.
- Noted.

478
00:40:40,170 --> 00:40:42,480
- Make me look chic.
- Got it.

479
00:40:42,480 --> 00:40:45,130
- Did you get the shot?
- Let's take one more.

480
00:40:46,080 --> 00:40:47,440
- Okay.
- Post it.

481
00:40:47,440 --> 00:40:49,340
- Hashtag, daily.
- Okay.

482
00:40:49,340 --> 00:40:51,000
- Hashtag, every day.
- All right.

483
00:40:51,000 --> 00:40:52,560
- Hashtag, Seol Ak.
- Okay.

484
00:40:52,560 --> 00:40:55,140
Hashtag... what?

485
00:40:56,010 --> 00:40:59,130
- Isn't he the man who got five cases?
- Yes.

486
00:41:00,420 --> 00:41:03,330
Who's the new face?

487
00:41:04,110 --> 00:41:06,320
Don't tell me he's my rival?

488
00:41:06,320 --> 00:41:09,860
He doesn't look hip like us.

489
00:41:33,820 --> 00:41:35,830
Are you okay?

490
00:41:38,630 --> 00:41:42,980
I'm trying... to be okay.

491
00:41:42,980 --> 00:41:48,490
He's your long-time friend who helped you with this.

492
00:41:48,490 --> 00:41:51,570
You probably don't want to accept it.

493
00:41:51,570 --> 00:41:55,970
He did it for the company and his employees.

494
00:41:56,900 --> 00:42:01,820
I'm trying to tell myself that he had no other choice.

495
00:42:01,820 --> 00:42:03,700
My father protected IM for a long time

496
00:42:03,700 --> 00:42:07,480
as a businessman.

497
00:42:07,480 --> 00:42:10,770
It's making me ask myself

498
00:42:10,770 --> 00:42:13,420
how he endured all those years.

499
00:42:14,190 --> 00:42:19,440
Yong Mun Gu will know all the information we know now.

500
00:42:20,790 --> 00:42:24,390
I'm sorry, Prosecutor Do.

501
00:42:27,420 --> 00:42:32,980
Starting now, we have to become stronger.

502
00:42:32,980 --> 00:42:38,230
Yong Mun Gu is now as big an enemy to us as No Hwa Yeong.

503
00:42:38,970 --> 00:42:40,580
Yes.

504
00:42:58,860 --> 00:43:02,740
Hey, Pyeon. Is that the only pair of glasses you own?

505
00:43:03,880 --> 00:43:07,000
Don't be such a cheap loser.

506
00:43:07,000 --> 00:43:10,140
Ask your mom to send you a pair.

507
00:43:10,930 --> 00:43:13,440
I went to try it while I was on leave

508
00:43:13,440 --> 00:43:16,150
so I can make a scene once I'm discharged.

509
00:43:16,150 --> 00:43:20,560
- It seemed like she hurt her legs.
- Aigoo.

510
00:43:22,010 --> 00:43:24,290
Do you have your cellphone with you?

511
00:43:24,290 --> 00:43:25,160
What?

512
00:43:25,160 --> 00:43:27,020
I need to call my mom.

513
00:43:27,020 --> 00:43:28,960
What are you suddenly talking about, you punk?

514
00:43:28,960 --> 00:43:31,440
I need to check that my mom is safe.

515
00:43:31,440 --> 00:43:35,960
Once Sergeant Ma is discharged, then my mom...

516
00:43:35,960 --> 00:43:37,580
My mom...

517
00:43:37,580 --> 00:43:40,410
Get it together, you punk.

518
00:43:41,340 --> 00:43:43,350
Hey. Are you playing games with me?

519
00:43:43,350 --> 00:43:45,520
Once Sergeant Ma gets discharged,

520
00:43:45,520 --> 00:43:48,340
he said he would harm my mom.

521
00:43:48,340 --> 00:43:51,350
My mom... if she hurt her legs again,

522
00:43:51,350 --> 00:43:53,820
she won't ever walk again.

523
00:43:57,800 --> 00:44:00,200
Sergeant Ma is sleeping right now, you punk.

524
00:44:00,200 --> 00:44:02,380
Get it together!

525
00:44:04,020 --> 00:44:06,380
Sergeant Ma hasn't been discharged?

526
00:44:07,110 --> 00:44:08,430
You punk.

527
00:44:08,430 --> 00:44:10,370
Let it go.

528
00:44:10,370 --> 00:44:14,610
Let go. One, two—

529
00:44:14,610 --> 00:44:16,740
You bastard.

530
00:44:41,680 --> 00:44:45,560
I'll return to duty after I find Sergeant Ma.

531
00:44:45,560 --> 00:44:47,590
Unity.

532
00:44:52,730 --> 00:44:54,560
The ambulance approached me,

533
00:44:54,560 --> 00:44:56,220
so I fainted like this.

534
00:44:56,220 --> 00:44:57,480
After I fainted,

535
00:44:57,480 --> 00:45:00,590
- the EMT took me away in the ambulance.
- I see.

536
00:45:01,400 --> 00:45:03,790
Where is Sergeant Ma?

537
00:45:05,480 --> 00:45:08,330
- What?
- I didn't hear you say "sir."

538
00:45:08,330 --> 00:45:09,470
Do I look like your peer?

539
00:45:09,470 --> 00:45:11,420
I thought I heard Ma's voice.

540
00:45:11,420 --> 00:45:14,170
Where are your manners, you punk?

541
00:45:14,170 --> 00:45:17,920
Hey. This may be his last year, but he's still your superior.

542
00:45:17,920 --> 00:45:19,600
Where is he?

543
00:45:19,600 --> 00:45:23,180
Aren't you on duty though?

544
00:45:24,160 --> 00:45:25,700
Who's rifle is that?

545
00:45:25,700 --> 00:45:30,360
Wait, good point. Why does the idiot have two rifles?

546
00:45:42,500 --> 00:45:45,960
This punk completely lost his mind.

547
00:45:45,960 --> 00:45:50,540
Man, what are you doing?

548
00:45:50,540 --> 00:45:52,550
You're going to shoot us?

549
00:45:52,550 --> 00:45:55,760
Cut the crap, we know you can't pull the trigger.

550
00:45:55,760 --> 00:46:00,700
- Hey. Shoot us. Do it.
- Go ahead then.

551
00:46:03,030 --> 00:46:07,350
Get it together, you punk. Do you have a death wish?

552
00:46:18,950 --> 00:46:23,290
That's it. That's the Pyeon we know.

553
00:46:23,290 --> 00:46:28,440
Good boy, Pyeon-kachu. Get going.

554
00:46:32,760 --> 00:46:34,780
I told you to leave.

555
00:46:37,390 --> 00:46:39,830
He needs a good slapping to learn.

556
00:46:39,830 --> 00:46:42,550
What an idiot.

557
00:46:42,550 --> 00:46:44,370
- Let's eat.
- Let's carry on eating.

558
00:46:44,370 --> 00:46:49,650
- He's only good at being Pikachu.
- Yes, he's good at that.

559
00:46:49,650 --> 00:46:53,840
- Yes, he is.
- At least he's got that.

560
00:46:53,840 --> 00:46:56,260
- The 100,000 volts—
- Grenade!

561
00:46:58,540 --> 00:47:00,980
I won't put up with this anymore.

562
00:47:00,980 --> 00:47:05,380
If I do, my mom will be in danger.

563
00:47:09,300 --> 00:47:11,960
Pyeon Sang Ho! What the hell are you doing?

564
00:47:23,950 --> 00:47:27,810
- What's this sound?
- Aren't those gunshots?

565
00:47:27,810 --> 00:47:30,090
Which psychopath is it?

566
00:47:30,090 --> 00:47:32,160
Hey, go and check.

567
00:47:33,510 --> 00:47:36,040
I said go out and check!

568
00:47:36,040 --> 00:47:38,410
You, No Tae Nam! You go.

569
00:47:38,410 --> 00:47:42,240
- Hurry up, you punk!
- Get going!

570
00:47:44,280 --> 00:47:46,440
- Is Sergeant Ma here?
- You bastard—

571
00:47:50,270 --> 00:47:52,130
He's not here either.

572
00:48:01,350 --> 00:48:03,810
Rifle!

573
00:48:05,360 --> 00:48:07,230
He's not here either.

574
00:48:15,770 --> 00:48:18,940
Go out and check, you punks!

575
00:48:18,940 --> 00:48:21,750
Bunch of idiots.

576
00:48:26,510 --> 00:48:27,580
Gather around me.

577
00:48:27,580 --> 00:48:31,010
Hurry up! Stick together.

578
00:48:42,110 --> 00:48:43,820
One.

579
00:48:44,940 --> 00:48:48,570
Two. Three!

580
00:48:57,080 --> 00:48:59,770
Is Sergeant Ma sleeping here?

581
00:48:59,770 --> 00:49:03,310
- I thought he was discharged.
- Pyeon.

582
00:49:03,310 --> 00:49:06,950
Have you gone mad? Put the gun down.

583
00:49:06,950 --> 00:49:11,870
- Put it down, you punk!
- Sergeant Ma! Sergeant Ma!

584
00:49:11,870 --> 00:49:15,300
What? He's not here.

585
00:49:15,300 --> 00:49:17,420
Did he really get discharged?

586
00:49:18,290 --> 00:49:20,120
Hey, calm down.

587
00:49:20,120 --> 00:49:22,000
Calm down. Let's talk about this, Sang Ho.

588
00:49:22,000 --> 00:49:24,000
Hey, Pyeon!

589
00:49:24,000 --> 00:49:26,160
No, Sang Ho.

590
00:49:26,160 --> 00:49:29,190
- Let's talk this out.
- You have no idea how torturous it was for me

591
00:49:29,190 --> 00:49:31,970
every time I was on duty with you, right?

592
00:49:32,680 --> 00:49:35,150
You're all the same!

593
00:49:52,780 --> 00:49:57,100
Private Pyeon. Please spare me.

594
00:49:57,100 --> 00:50:01,040
Hyeong Sang Ho! Please get it together!

595
00:50:08,550 --> 00:50:13,230
Only you treated me like a human being.

596
00:50:19,910 --> 00:50:24,640
You were bullied by Sergeant Ma too. Let's look for him together.

597
00:50:29,380 --> 00:50:31,520
Hyeong Sang Ho. Hyeong!

598
00:51:29,190 --> 00:51:33,070
Mother. M-M-Mom...

599
00:51:36,960 --> 00:51:38,890
What's going on?

600
00:51:40,030 --> 00:51:42,660
Please s-s-save me.

601
00:51:42,660 --> 00:51:45,640
What are you talking about?

602
00:51:47,520 --> 00:51:51,000
Please save me, Mom! Please!

603
00:51:51,000 --> 00:51:52,640
Tae Nam. Tae—

604
00:51:55,130 --> 00:51:57,060
Adjutant Yang!

605
00:51:59,330 --> 00:52:02,550
- Division Commander.
- Check in with 14th G.O.P.

606
00:52:02,550 --> 00:52:04,270
We actually just got a report

607
00:52:04,270 --> 00:52:06,470
that multiple gunshots have been heard from there.

608
00:52:08,260 --> 00:52:10,660
I'll get the car ready immediately.

609
00:52:19,160 --> 00:52:21,240
Save us!

610
00:52:36,980 --> 00:52:39,740
Sergeant Ma, are you here?

611
00:52:56,290 --> 00:52:58,670
I have one cubicle left.

612
00:52:58,670 --> 00:53:00,930
Hurry up and answer me.

613
00:53:19,150 --> 00:53:23,170
I'm sorry! I'm really sorry!

614
00:53:50,430 --> 00:53:52,130
Put down the gun.

615
00:53:52,970 --> 00:53:55,370
Put it down, you punk!

616
00:53:59,590 --> 00:54:01,710
Put it down and raise your arms.

617
00:54:28,260 --> 00:54:30,870
- Unity!
- Report immediately.

618
00:54:30,870 --> 00:54:33,310
It's been confirmed that it wasn't an attack from the North.

619
00:54:33,310 --> 00:54:35,900
We suspect it was one of our soldiers who went on a shooting spree.

620
00:54:35,900 --> 00:54:37,920
Shooting spree?

621
00:54:37,920 --> 00:54:39,070
How many survivors?

622
00:54:39,070 --> 00:54:42,400
The soldiers out on duty on the frontlines during the shooting survived.

623
00:54:42,400 --> 00:54:44,400
But many including the soldiers and officers

624
00:54:44,400 --> 00:54:46,900
who were sleeping in the barracks have died.

625
00:54:46,900 --> 00:54:51,110
Was Private No Tae Nam one of the survivors?

626
00:54:52,320 --> 00:54:54,340
- Answer me.
- Yes.

627
00:54:54,340 --> 00:54:57,010
He's one of them.

628
00:54:57,010 --> 00:54:59,390
But there was a confrontation with our men during the siege.

629
00:54:59,390 --> 00:55:02,160
So we handcuffed him and have him in custody.

630
00:55:02,160 --> 00:55:04,560
Private No Tae Nam in a confrontation?

631
00:55:04,560 --> 00:55:06,270
That's correct, Division Commander.

632
00:55:06,270 --> 00:55:08,160
Where is he now?

633
00:55:27,710 --> 00:55:29,570
Mother.

634
00:55:29,570 --> 00:55:30,640
M-Mom.

635
00:55:30,640 --> 00:55:34,010
M-Mom. Mom.

636
00:55:34,010 --> 00:55:37,050
Mom... Mom.

637
00:55:37,050 --> 00:55:38,980
- Give us some privacy.
- Mom...

638
00:55:38,980 --> 00:55:40,710
Yes, ma'am.

639
00:55:45,430 --> 00:55:48,540
Mom... Mom.

640
00:55:48,540 --> 00:55:52,320
Tae Nam. Did you do this?

641
00:55:53,140 --> 00:55:57,310
- What?
- I asked if you were the shooter from the mass shooting.

642
00:55:57,310 --> 00:55:59,700
Did this happen because of you?

643
00:56:00,480 --> 00:56:02,500
Hurry up and answer me!

644
00:56:03,310 --> 00:56:06,500
- It's not me.
- Are you sure?

645
00:56:07,550 --> 00:56:10,560
It's r-r-really not me.

646
00:56:10,560 --> 00:56:13,010
I didn't do it.

647
00:56:14,430 --> 00:56:16,130
That's a relief.

648
00:56:32,610 --> 00:56:34,380
Mom...

649
00:56:48,800 --> 00:56:50,750
Who is it so late?

650
00:56:53,990 --> 00:56:56,550
What's all the fuss? Is it urgent?

651
00:56:56,550 --> 00:56:59,240
There was a mass shooting incident at the frontline.

652
00:56:59,240 --> 00:57:01,310
You should head over now.

653
00:57:01,310 --> 00:57:02,550
What about Prosecutor Cha?

654
00:57:02,550 --> 00:57:04,270
She's waiting outside.

655
00:57:04,270 --> 00:57:06,340
Hurry on out.

656
00:57:11,170 --> 00:57:15,790
We'll talk about the Ministry of Defense and the defense industry the next time we meet.

657
00:57:15,790 --> 00:57:18,570
You'll understand just how big of a business it is

658
00:57:18,570 --> 00:57:20,780
that you stepped into.

659
00:57:20,780 --> 00:57:22,360
Great.

660
00:57:24,320 --> 00:57:28,760
Oh, I thought of this after I met up with the members of the Patriotic Society.

661
00:57:28,760 --> 00:57:33,590
Were there no files about them from what you got from Chairman Cha's property?

662
00:57:33,590 --> 00:57:35,370
A file?

663
00:57:37,230 --> 00:57:42,950
I guess Division Commander No kept a lot of things from you.

664
00:57:42,950 --> 00:57:44,870
Hurry up and tell me.

665
00:57:44,870 --> 00:57:48,550
Chairman Cha has a corruption file against the Patriotic Society.

666
00:57:48,550 --> 00:57:51,760
He called it the Patriotic Society's X-File.

667
00:57:52,640 --> 00:57:57,260
The Patriotic Society's X-File.

668
00:57:57,260 --> 00:58:00,780
There has been a mass shooting incident...

669
00:58:00,780 --> 00:58:03,150
at the 4th Infantry Division in Woncheol, Gangwon Province.

670
00:58:03,150 --> 00:58:05,810
It's been reported that multiple gunshots were heard.

671
00:58:05,810 --> 00:58:09,810
We anticipate that there will be a large number of fatalities. People are shocked to hear this news.

672
00:58:09,810 --> 00:58:13,850
Officials don't know the details of the case yet.

673
00:58:13,850 --> 00:58:18,540
The soldier who committed the crime was captured on site.

674
00:58:18,540 --> 00:58:21,040
According to the initial investigation done by the MPs

675
00:58:21,040 --> 00:58:23,950
the first explosion was heard here.

676
00:58:23,950 --> 00:58:26,580
It was in this common area.

677
00:58:35,430 --> 00:58:38,710
Do Not Enter

678
00:58:38,710 --> 00:58:42,650
They suspect Private Pyeon Sang Ho acted alone.

679
00:58:42,650 --> 00:58:47,690
But he didn't speak during the investigation. So the interrogation was brief.

680
00:58:47,690 --> 00:58:50,440
Pyeon Sang Ho. "I make myself."

681
00:58:58,720 --> 00:59:01,260
Where was Sergeant Pyeon Sang Ho arrested?

682
00:59:01,260 --> 00:59:04,590
In the bathroom. Follow me.

683
00:59:22,910 --> 00:59:25,330
I'm s-sorry. I'm sorry, okay?

684
00:59:25,330 --> 00:59:26,490
I was wrong!

685
00:59:26,490 --> 00:59:28,330
Pyeon! I'm sorry, Pyeon.

686
00:59:28,330 --> 00:59:31,160
I'm sorry! Truly!

687
00:59:34,120 --> 00:59:35,350
Save me.

688
00:59:35,350 --> 00:59:38,820
Say that you won't hurt my mom! Say it!

689
00:59:38,820 --> 00:59:41,380
Say it! Say it!!

690
00:59:42,210 --> 00:59:43,950
Say it!

691
00:59:43,950 --> 00:59:45,950
Say it!

692
01:00:13,860 --> 01:00:16,940
Section Chief Ahn said he's ready to be interrogated.

693
01:00:16,940 --> 01:00:19,860
You said he didn't say a word to the MP's?

694
01:00:19,860 --> 01:00:21,420
Yes, sir.

695
01:00:40,910 --> 01:00:44,040
Unit, name and rank.

696
01:00:47,490 --> 01:00:49,590
Private Pyeon?

697
01:00:55,610 --> 01:00:57,550
Private Pyeon.

698
01:01:00,220 --> 01:01:03,580
You miss your mom, right?

699
01:01:04,660 --> 01:01:07,900
It's all right, just answer.

700
01:01:07,900 --> 01:01:11,580
No, it's okay.

701
01:01:13,180 --> 01:01:15,120
Get up.

702
01:01:15,920 --> 01:01:18,160
Your mother is outside.

703
01:01:18,160 --> 01:01:19,850
I called her.

704
01:01:19,850 --> 01:01:23,310
R-Really?

705
01:01:27,710 --> 01:01:30,120
Pyeon Sang Ho

706
01:01:30,120 --> 01:01:34,740
What is it? Are you finding it hard to face her?

707
01:01:49,000 --> 01:01:51,610
Sang Ho.

708
01:01:51,610 --> 01:01:53,380
Mom.

709
01:02:01,110 --> 01:02:04,680
Sang Ho. Why did you do it?

710
01:02:04,680 --> 01:02:07,470
Why? You're a good kid. Tell me.

711
01:02:07,470 --> 01:02:09,630
Why did you do it?

712
01:02:19,080 --> 01:02:22,080
You should've endured it a little more.

713
01:02:23,720 --> 01:02:26,360
Just a little more.

714
01:02:28,250 --> 01:02:30,530
Mom...

715
01:02:30,530 --> 01:02:32,800
What are we going to do?

716
01:02:33,770 --> 01:02:36,290
My poor son.

717
01:02:42,950 --> 01:02:46,150
4th Infantry Division, 24th Unit.

718
01:02:46,150 --> 01:02:49,460
1st Battalion 3rd Platoon. Private Pyeon Sang Ho.

719
01:02:49,460 --> 01:02:54,380
I'll read the charges against you from the MP's investigations.

720
01:02:55,600 --> 01:02:58,280
Murdering a superior, attempted murder of superior,

721
01:02:58,280 --> 01:03:00,070
tampering and theft of military goods,

722
01:03:00,070 --> 01:03:02,890
dereliction of duty, criminal homicide,

723
01:03:02,890 --> 01:03:05,080
attempted murder.

724
01:03:10,310 --> 01:03:12,850
- Who's your accomplice?
- I don't have one.

725
01:03:12,850 --> 01:03:15,080
I did it alone.

726
01:03:15,080 --> 01:03:17,360
What was your motive?

727
01:03:19,600 --> 01:03:21,830
Your motive.

728
01:03:25,780 --> 01:03:30,620
They're all dead now, so does it even matter?

729
01:03:33,440 --> 01:03:36,860
Your sentencing depends on your motive.

730
01:03:36,860 --> 01:03:40,520
It's important if your crime was planned or accidental.

731
01:03:40,520 --> 01:03:43,000
Why do you think the motive for the crime is unimportant?

732
01:03:43,000 --> 01:03:44,860
Everything...

733
01:03:45,960 --> 01:03:48,150
Everything is just an excuse.

734
01:03:48,150 --> 01:03:50,840
Because they're all dead?

735
01:03:56,660 --> 01:03:59,390
That's enough for today.

736
01:04:16,280 --> 01:04:19,050
It's the updated list of the deceased.

737
01:04:19,050 --> 01:04:20,170
Victims of 4th Division GOP Mass Shooting Case

738
01:04:20,170 --> 01:04:24,380
The remaining survivors are resting and being treated at the military hospital.
Sergeant Ahn Su Ho

739
01:04:24,380 --> 01:04:26,780
Private No Tae Nam is there too.

740
01:04:26,780 --> 01:04:29,690
- No Tae Nam?
- Yes.

741
01:04:31,050 --> 01:04:33,000
Let's head over.

742
01:04:35,770 --> 01:04:39,720
Korean Armed Forces Capital Hospital

743
01:04:39,720 --> 01:04:42,610
You all understand, right?

744
01:04:42,610 --> 01:04:45,010
We'll be investigated by military prosecutors now.

745
01:04:45,010 --> 01:04:49,950
Why should we have to lie for you?

746
01:04:49,950 --> 01:04:52,630
You're saying it's all on me?

747
01:04:52,630 --> 01:04:54,130
Of course.

748
01:04:54,130 --> 01:04:56,870
You were the one who bullied Pyeon every single day.

749
01:04:56,870 --> 01:05:00,020
Don't try to throw me under the bus. You did it too!

750
01:05:00,020 --> 01:05:02,260
What about you? And you.

751
01:05:02,260 --> 01:05:05,630
You all turned the other way.

752
01:05:05,630 --> 01:05:09,140
Listen, what did we do wrong?

753
01:05:09,140 --> 01:05:11,100
We're the victims.

754
01:05:11,100 --> 01:05:15,090
Pyeon Sang Ho, that psycho tried to kill all of us.

755
01:05:15,090 --> 01:05:18,610
Hey, No Tae Nam. You'll cooperate, right?

756
01:05:18,610 --> 01:05:20,630
Your mom is the Division Commander.

757
01:05:20,630 --> 01:05:23,830
You know what'll happen to your mom if you don't, right?

758
01:05:29,850 --> 01:05:31,530
Be smart about it.

759
01:05:31,530 --> 01:05:34,070
Nothing happened.

760
01:05:34,070 --> 01:05:37,540
Or else we'll take the fall for everything, got it?

761
01:05:38,610 --> 01:05:41,070
Mark my words.

762
01:05:41,070 --> 01:05:42,550
Okay, sir.

763
01:05:48,930 --> 01:05:50,800
Chairman.

